{"id": "EUVD-2024-52027", "enisaUuid": "a0cf443a-05ac-3599-9581-29ebb31847ca", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nregulator: axp20x: AXP717: set ramp_delay\n\nAXP717 datasheet says that regulator ramp delay is 15.625 us/step,\nwhich is 10mV in our case.\n\nAdd a AXP_DESC_RANGES_DELAY macro and update AXP_DESC_RANGES macro to\nexpand to AXP_DESC_RANGES_DELAY with ramp_delay = 0\n\nFor DCDC4, steps is 100mv\n\nAdd a AXP_DESC_DELAY macro and update AXP_DESC macro to\nexpand to AXP_DESC_DELAY with ramp_delay = 0\n\nThis patch fix crashes when using CPU DVFS.", "datePublished": "2025-01-11T15:30:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-15T21:31:38", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/10eb845a87193ef922cd002e0ff4f4759c1e918d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f07ae52f5cf6a5584fdf7c8c652f027d90bc8b74", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53682"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53682"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2dcb8958-dda7-30df-bfd7-8d41cb6c38df", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.10"}, {"id": "3ca47e17-d686-3538-81b9-34764f5687dc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d2ac3df75c3a995064cfac0171e082a30d8c4c66 <f07ae52f5cf6a5584fdf7c8c652f027d90bc8b74"}, {"id": "6c1e5fab-cffc-30fd-8b5a-a9a8057d7c75", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d2ac3df75c3a995064cfac0171e082a30d8c4c66 <10eb845a87193ef922cd002e0ff4f4759c1e918d"}, {"id": "9843383d-ee64-380e-ace0-ba8daff109d3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "cb045d3d-1ad0-3753-8e7e-2335c5de8722", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "dba05b38-47e0-313a-b520-b1d22ff3cfc1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.6"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "989f14d3-5548-33ad-aa85-8b282d42b9a1", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}